#          
def find_col_with_value(df, value):
    for col in df:
        if (df[col] == value).any():
             return col

#  index 
for i in range(len(csv_list)):
  a = find_col_with_value(globals()['data{}'.format(i)], "")
  globals()['data{}'.format(i)].set_index(a, inplace = True)

In [33]:
#  

def draw_data(x, color):
  m.choropleth(
      geo_data=state_geo,
      name=x,
      data=df,
      columns=["", x],
      key_on='feature.properties.name',
      fill_color=color,
      fill_opacity = 0.9,
      line_opacity = 0.6,
      color = 'gray',
      legend = True,
      legend_name = x
  )

def scatter_draw(x):
  plt.scatter(df[""], df[x], color = 'black')
  plt.xlabel("")
  plt.ylabel(x)
